In heavy saucepan, heat vegetable oil over medium heat until warm. Add onions and garlic and saute until soft. Add beef and salt. Cook until beef is browned throughout. Drain excess fat. Add chili, cumin, Worcestershire, tomato sauce, sugar and water. Bring pot to low boil and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add BUSH'S(R) BEST Dark Red Kidney Beans and simmer 15 minutes. Add Tabasco sauce to taste, and more salt if desired. Top with shredded cheese and serve with crackers.